𝗧𝗼𝗽 𝟱 𝗝𝗮𝘃𝗮 𝗣𝗼𝗱𝗰𝗮𝘀𝘁𝘀 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗝𝗮𝘃𝗮 𝗱𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗹𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝗶𝗻 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟰


Podcasting has become a widely popular medium for sharing ideas, stories, and knowledge. It allows individuals to connect with listeners from all around the world and create a community centered around their interests.

Podcasts even make learning easier & fun. Imagine being stuck in traffic on your way to work, but instead of just waiting, you’re getting inspired by great stories from fellow developers – all thanks to podcasts! Whether one is looking to learn new tricks, share a laugh with fellow devs, or just stay updated, these podcasts have something for you.


Here's a list of my personal favorite Java podcasts. Enjoy!!


𝙰̲ ̲𝙱̲𝚘̲𝚘̲𝚝̲𝚒̲𝚏̲𝚞̲𝚕̲ ̲𝙿̲𝚘̲𝚍̲𝚌̲𝚊̲𝚜̲𝚝̲

https://lnkd.in/grwRs4Di

Hosted by the extremely humorous & knowledgeable Josh Long, this podcast covers a wide range of topics related to Spring, Java and software development. Each episode features interviews with industry experts, thought leaders & fellow developers who share their experiences, tips & tricks.


𝙵̲𝚘̲𝚘̲𝚓̲𝚊̲𝚢̲ ̲𝙿̲𝚘̲𝚍̲𝚌̲𝚊̲𝚜̲𝚝̲

https://lnkd.in/gZXRFzxy

Hosted by the very generous Frank Delporte, this podcast explores everything from deep technical topics to broader industry trends, offering something for Java developers at all levels. http://foojay.io/ is a vibrant community where Java developers can also read articles and connect with others who share their passion for Java.


𝚃̲𝚑̲𝚎̲ ̲𝚂̲𝚝̲𝚊̲𝚌̲𝚔̲ ̲𝙾̲𝚟̲𝚎̲𝚛̲𝚏̲𝚕̲𝚘̲𝚠̲ ̲𝙿̲𝚘̲𝚍̲𝚌̲𝚊̲𝚜̲𝚝̲

https://lnkd.in/gzCuznge

Hosted by the amazing trio of Ryan Donovan, Benjamin Popper & Eira Long May, this podcast discusses about topics ranging from the latest languages to industry buzz. The hosts keep it lively with expert guests & exciting tech anecdotes.


𝙹̲𝚊̲𝚟̲𝚊̲ ̲𝙿̲𝚞̲𝚋̲ ̲𝙷̲𝚘̲𝚞̲𝚜̲𝚎̲

https://lnkd.in/g4uR_Qfa

Hosted by Bob Paulin & Freddy Guime, two of the most passionate developers in the Java community bring to us an informative podcast exploring new tech like GraalVM, breaking down real-world coding challenges & spark discussions around complex topics like reactive programming.


𝙹̲𝚊̲𝚟̲𝚊̲ ̲𝙾̲𝚏̲𝚏̲–̲𝙷̲𝚎̲𝚊̲𝚙̲

https://lnkd.in/geWyPZnb

Hosted by a passionate group of Java developers, including Freddy Guime, Bob Paulin, Michael Minella & Josh Juneau where they explore Java, JVM internals & software architecture while also chatting about industry news with a touch of humor. It’s a fun and informative mix.



Podcasts have turned out to be extremely powerful tools for learning. Whether you're looking to learn something new, stay informed on the latest trends, or just be entertained, there’s a tech podcast out there that suits your needs. You never know which one might become your favorite.



𝘛𝘶𝘯𝘦 𝘪𝘯 & 𝘩𝘢𝘱𝘱𝘺 𝘭𝘪𝘴𝘵𝘦𝘯𝘪𝘯g!!



